<br>
1-  Solons Bewitching Bravura<br>
2-  /assist &lt;name&gt;<br>
3-  /pet attack<br>
4-  Manasong/VoV<br>
<br>
It works pretty easily.  Start off with /assist, and then switch off to a different target.  Hit the &quot;1&quot; hotkey.  As soon as the creature is charmed, hit 2-3-4 in rapid succession.  This gets your pet on the proper assist target, and pumps up another simple song to help your target.  At this point, hit f1-f1, and back up.  Recharm when necessary, and repeat.<br>
<br>
Maybe if they fix pixie strike and lullaby, I can use them too.<br>
<br>
I was doing this last night in Venril Sathirs room, deep in Karnor.  Was damn fun, and quite effective- I got the majority of the kill shots :-) <p></p><i>Edited by <A HREF=http://pub12.ezboard.com/ukaluianismyname.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kaluian is my name</A> at: 8/19/00 3:34:09 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#242422><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub12.ezboard.com/ukaluianismyname.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kaluian is my name</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>   <font color=#6FB8DD>(8/19/00 3:33 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub40.ezboard.com/fthesaryrntavernclassdiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=42.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Charming in group</span><hr size=1> err, another simple song to help your group.  Sorry. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub12.ezboard.com/uandvarishadowmist.showPublicProfile?language=EN>AndvariShadowmist</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>   <font color=#6FB8DD>(8/19/00 6:04 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub40.ezboard.com/fthesaryrntavernclassdiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=42.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Charming in group</span><hr size=1> The problem with this is when the mobs are pretty much stacked. Hard to know which one is the main tank's target and which one to charm when they are the same kind of mobs.<br>
