<br>
I think 4 is the typical max song twist for most bards in ordinary situations.  When I'm in a Plane or somewhere else with multiple groups, often I get a bit of slowdown and am reduced to playing only 3 songs.  Against dragons and gods, when slowdown increases more, I move down to 2 songs- also because usually, the songs are very important, and I don't want anything to drop, even for a second.<br>
<br>
Also, if you get a Breath of Harmony or some other item which procs a bard song (like the monks robe), you can instantly add another song to your twist.  With both the Breath and the Robe, the effect is right-clickable, and it lasts for one pulse- the same as playing the song.  However, it has INSTANT casting time, and no recast delay.  So my twist is often 1 (3 seconds) 2 (3 seconds) 3 (3 seconds) 4 (3 seconds) 5-1 (3 seconds)....<br>
<br>
Another advantage to the weapon is that it basically allows you a 9th spell slot.  Since you have Nivs on your weapon, you don't need to keep it memorized, and you have room for something else.  Although, when you switch to an instrument, it does drop Nivs- I haven't tested to see if the effect is right-clickable yet.<br>
<br>
